250 g Ground Turkey
170 g Orzo
¼ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
56 g Baby Spinach
5 g Italian Herb Spice Blend
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
113 mL Cream
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
1 unit(s) Lemon
1 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Oil*
½ tsp Salt*
½ tsp Pepper*
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Butter*

Before starting, preheat a large pot over medium.
Wash and dry produce.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
Mince or grate garlic.
Juice half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings). Cut any remaining lemon into wedges.

To the pot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey. Cook 3-4 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add garlic, peppers and Italian Herb Spice Blend. Cook for 2 min, stirring often, until peppers are tender-crisp.

Add orzo. Cook for 1 min, stirring often.
Add tomato sauce base, chicken stock concentrate, pesto, cream and 2 cups (4 cups) water. Bring to a simmer.
Once simmering, reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook for 10-12 min, stirring often, until most of the liquid is absorbed and orzo is tender.

When orzo is done, remove from heat.
To the pot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, half the Parmesan, lemon juice and spinach. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Divide turkey-orzo mixture between bowls.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top.